7.1.2 - W11SR02: Non-Compliance with Windows 11 Hardening Blueprints
ISM controls:
•	Control: 1416; Revision: 3; Updated: Dec-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Hardening standard operating environments)
•	Control: 1448; Revision: 3; Updated: Dec-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Configuring operating systems)
•	Control: 0314; Revision: 6; Updated: Jun-21; Applicability: All; OS: All (Change management processes)
________________________________________
Current Risk
Insufficient, incomplete implementation or deviation from the ASD and Microsoft Authentication and System Hardening Blueprint for Windows 11, may lead to compromise of the agency system and / or its data.
Risk Assessment:
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
ALMOST CERTAIN	x	MAJOR	=	EXTREME
________________________________________
Recommendations:
1.	Mandate Baseline Alignment: Formally adopt the Australian Signals Directorate (ASD) Windows 11 Hardening Blueprint as the mandatory minimum security standard for all agency workstations.
2.	Automated Compliance Auditing: Deploy configuration management tools (e.g., Microsoft Intune or Group Policy Analytics) to continuously monitor and report on deviations from the established hardening baseline.
3.	Establish Exception Governance: Implement a formal risk-acceptance process for any technical requirements that necessitate a deviation from the hardening blueprint, ensuring such risks are reviewed annually.
- Treatment #1
•	Baseline Deployment: Utilise Microsoft Security Compliance Toolkit to apply recommended security baselines to all Windows 11 endpoints, covering kernel DMA protection, virtualization-based security, and credential guard.
•	Security Feature Enforcement: Enable hardware-backed security features including TPM 2.0, Secure Boot, and UEFI protection to establish a root of trust.
•	Vulnerability Management Integration: Link hardening compliance data to the agency’s vulnerability management platform to prioritise remediation of non-compliant assets.
________________________________________
Residual risk outcome if recommendation is implemented.
Aligning the workstation environment with industry-recognised hardening blueprints significantly raises the cost for an adversary to gain a foothold. While the "Major" consequence of a system compromise remains due to the nature of agency information, the systematic application of technical controls reduces the likelihood of a successful exploit from "Almost Certain" to "Rare."
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
RARE	x	MAJOR	=	MEDIUM

